Quote: ... their dresses consisted of the kaitaka and karowai, made of silky flax, and covered with dog-skin mats, or  neris [sic: e-acute] made of rushes, as protection against rain. <i>Ibid.</i> 1/177-178 A valuable garment for the stormy [178] climate of the southward is called neri[e-acute], and is made of undressed flax or of the kierakiki, a species of rush, impervious to rain.
